details.description:
The Percantile and Creamery is the premier Coffee, Ice Cream, and Dessert Bar in the Charlotte metro area. We are thrilling people with our amazing interior design, our incredible customer service, and the quality of our offerings. We have a beautifully designed 1920’s Mercantile-themed monochromatic throwback, where people feel excited by their surroundings, and blown away by their treats. Great for business meetings, families, couples, and you! Ask us about room rentals for meetings, events, or parties! Now offering catering.
Nestled next to Concord Mills Mall, behind Verizon, and in the same building as McAlister’s in Concord, NC!

reviews_data.review_text: Estaba bueno el café, el mejor del area

reviews_data.review_text: Good options, great atmosphere. Went on a Saturday at around 4pm and they had already run out of some ice cream flavors. Got salted caramel and cookies & cream, both were excellent.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks Khurram! We are so happy you enjoyed the ice cream. We are fully stocked now! We usually order only once a week during “Winter”, but we are slowly starting to order ice cream 2x/week! So hopefully we do a better job with stocking. We appreciate you.

reviews_data.review_text: Coffee was great but on our first visit today we had  several issues. Wasn’t open based on the hours of 7, opened shortly after 7. Mobile ordering doesn’t work till 7:30 not 7. We wanted a waffle but they were out of those. Took over 20 minutes for 2 coffees and we were the first to order for the day. Staff was friendly but not a great first visit. It is very nice inside and for a local based store to have mobile ordering and a touch screen ordering inside was a nice touch.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hey CH! This is concerning to hear. And we are sorry for this experience. We DO open at 7:00, and had no idea that one of my employees was late in opening. This will be addressed. 
Thank you for the heads up on the mobile ordering. That has been changed to 7:00 AM!
And the coffees taking 20 minutes is unacceptable. Is there any way you can tell me what day you came in? Please let us know here or email me at: sean@thepercantileandcreamery.com

I can assure you this will be fixed.  We hope you can give us another chance!

reviews_data.review_text: This was one of the greatest experiences in my life. The host was terrific and the place was very convenient. I would definitely recommend anyone to come here.

reviews_data.review_text: Used to be much better. Med latte, med iced coffee & very tiny pastry $16. And absolutely no care given in presentation and delivery. No porcelain cup, No design poured, just mixed into paper cup and slammed out to customer. For that price and ZERO customer experience. We're done here. Other places popping up that show they actually care and care about your visit and offer a delightful atmosphere. Like Mattie Ruths. This place has gotten just plain apathetic and totally lost their unique niche. So sad. Good riddance.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hey J. That is terrible to hear. I can assure you this is a one off. 
We do care very much. I would love to know more about your experience. We offer ceramic cups, and the cashier should’ve asked when you ordered.  Our prices haven’t changed barely at all since we opened, but I can understand you didn’t get the value you were looking for. I’m sorry for that. Please send me an email so we can get to the bottom of this. Sean@thepercantileandcreamery.com

Thank you!

reviews_data.review_text:
Really cute place great drinks, but to order an egg, cheese, and light on the mayo to only receive the bread and egg is disappointing 😞 what happened to the cheese and mayo? I will continue to come for the coffee...

Update: thank you for making it right. We came in and everyone was so sweet perusal. Polite enough to remake the sandwich. You guys stop by and grab a coffee you'll not be disappointed with the service or the coffee. Thank you again for fixing what I know was just an honest mistake.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hey J.!
Thanks for the positive review!
We are so sorry about the breakfast sandwich. We definitely make mistakes sometimes. Did you alert the team? They would have surely either fixed it or made you a new one! Next time, if I am around, I’ll comp you a sandwich. Let me know!

-Sean

reviews_data.review_text:
The coffee was not good. Staff did not know what a cortado was despite being on the menu and was given too large of a drink. The milk was burnt/over steamed and when I asked for an alternative milk, regular milk was still used and I ended up paying the price for it later...
The shop was clean and had a nice atmosphere.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hey Jake! That is terrible to hear. I personally apologize. To hear that my staff doesn’t know what a Cortado is or what it looks like is very bizarre. We have very strict training. Yes, we have some new people, but it is very bothersome. 
It seems as though they gave you the wrong drink. Meaning you got someone else’s drink by mistake. I would be very curious as to when you came in and if you gave my staff feedback. We are always happy to fix it. Can you send me a quick email to sean@thepercantileandcreamery.com or a message through Instagram. As a lactose intolerant person, this is a big mistake that I want to fix. Again, I’m sorry. Thanks !

-Sean

Please email me directly at:
Sean@thepercantileandcreamery.com

reviews_data.review_text: Five star in every bucket!!

reviews_data.review_text:
Last night my husband and I went for a dessert date after dinner. The atmosphere was very calm and vibrant with lots of couples and families.  We were so glad that they were open.  I enjoyed the best Green tea Matcha latte made by Sama.  She was so kind and generous.  She was able to customize it by adding mint flavor.  I spoke to her at the end of the night and complimented the tea. 🍵 I mentioned how much for a refill, and she bless my heart and gave up her complementary shift drink. Hats off to the kind young man who worked at the register last night because he was so very patient as we were trying to figure out our order. Love this place!
🎄🍵❤️🍨🍁
reviews_data.owner_answer: That is amazing! Thank you so much for the kind review! I’ll share with them now!

reviews_data.review_text: I had a cappuccino and a cronut. The cronut was really good! Light, airy, and fluffy. The cappuccino was also food. Not amazing but would go again if I needed a solid one. Staff was friendly and nice but took a bit longer than I thought it would given they weren’t very busy.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks Russel for the fair review. We appreciate the feedback!

reviews_data.review_text: I got the honey and cinnamon latte and a scoop of oatmeal ice cream. It was soooooooo good. The cashier was super friendly and nice. The atmosphere was perfect for getting some school work done
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much Jessie! The Bee’s Knees is a customer favorite. And the oatmeal cream pie ice cream is crazy good. We appreciate you so much!

reviews_data.review_text: What a great experience at The Percantile and Creamery! The atmosphere is cozy, and the service was friendly and welcoming. I ordered a cappuccino, but I received a shot of espresso instead. Not a big deal, though, the waffle sundae more than made up for it! It was absolutely delicious—crispy, warm, and topped with just the right amount of sweetness. My wife really enjoyed her latte, which was perfectly balanced, and my son had a blast with the brownie sundae. He couldn't stop raving about it! Overall, the desserts were the highlight of our visit. Definitely recommend this place if you're in the area! We'll be back for sure the next time we are through the area.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hi Joe! Thanks so much for the great review! We are so happy you guys got a few different items to try out! Hopefully you were able to get a remake on your Cap. 
We appreciate the kind words!

reviews_data.review_text: The slowwwwwest experience I've ever had.  Over 15 mins for a cortado
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hey Josh! I’m so sorry to hear about the slow service. We try to set expectations on how many drinks we have when people order. Saturdays and Sundays (today) we were and usually are busy. With that said, we have 2 baristas doing their best to make quality drinks with the best speed they can make them. Hopefully the service was kind and the drink was good. Expectations should be anywhere from 5-10 minutes give or take on weekends. We will talk to the team today to make sure we are being as efficient as possible! Thanks for your feedback and we hope we can do better for you next time.

reviews_data.review_text:
Replying to the percentile .
I came by at least 4-5 more times after my review and it kept getting worse and worse . I finally messaged you guys and complained and questioned the barista , and was told in store and on Instagram that you guys use a CONCENTRATE AND HAVE ALWAYS USED A CONCENTRATE .  Making it seem like i was wrong and crazy . In this reply you mentioned beans . You guys lied . Someone lied to me … you never use to use a concentrate because I watched you make my drink . Now it’s all white , and sweet . Disgustingly sweet . I’m confused . Was the owner trying to make excuse for the baristas ? Or were you trying something new ? I use to buy the beans you used with the drinks !  Something isn’t right … just like the concentrate they put in my drink !

love percentile , but first time in 6-7 years , the berries didn’t taste like the berries . We drove over an hour for you guys … I can’t give you guys a bad rating , but I hope quality doesn’t change . Baristas have always been consistent. ALWAYS .

Hey!
Well you know, coming for the past 6 years, that consistency is our top priority. I’m sad to hear that. We haven’t changed the syrups or our beans. When did you come in? I can speak with the barista to see if something was different. Also, we are ALWAYS happy to remake your drink for you. Thanks for being a loyal customer! Would love to give you a free one next time. 

-Sean

Can you email me and let me know what you mean by concentrate?

We use Chai concentrate. 
But for our lattes we use freshly roasted and grounded beans from jags Head. 
My email is sean@thepercantileandcreamery.com

reviews_data.review_text: Don't come looking for dessert. This is a cofee ship. Despite the looks of the desserts the cakes we tried were dry and the frosting is hard like sugar candies you put on a birthday cake. Service was cool.

Appreciate the feedback. Glad the service was cool. Hopefully we can earn more stars next time.

reviews_data.review_text: This has to be one of the most consistent coffee shops in the Charlotte/Concord area. Over the last 6 years, I have NEVER had a bad drink here! If you're ever near Concord Mills, check this place out!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much Andy!

Correct, we love dogs. I am personally a huge dog fan and have been an owner for over 20 years. However, we cannot have dogs inside our establishment because we serve food.

Here is the regulation:

Country of Origin:  United States
Citation:  15A NCAC 18A.2656
Agency Origin:  Environmental Quality
Last Checked:  February, 2022
Summary: This North Carolina regulation makes amendments to the Food Code related to dogs and cats in outdoor dining areas. Dogs and cats are allowed in outdoor dining areas provided the dogs or cats are physically restrained and do not pass through the indoor area of the food establishment. All live animals, including pet cats and dogs, are not permitted to come into physical contact with any serving food, serving dishes, tableware, linens, utensils, or other food service items. Employees of a food establishment who prepare or handle food must not physically contact any live animals.

With that said, I apologize for the confusion as we do have young employees, many high school, and many newer.

And as always, you are welcome to come back any time and we will be happy to serve your pup some whipped cream!

Country of Origin:  United States
Citation:  15A NCAC 18A.2656
Agency Origin:  Environmental Quality
Last Checked:  February, 2022

I have a long, speckled history with this coffeeshop, but it's survived both good and bad.
First thing's first, the coffee is consistently great, especially when Grayson is on bar - she's by far my favorite barista in the area, and she brings both hospitality and expertise to the coffeeshop. Perc also offers Jags Head, and while I don't prefer their proprietary blend, I LOVE the coffee from their Finca el Cipres farm; it's one of my favorite roasts available in the Charlotte area. Furthermore, Perc offers excellent traditional espresso drinks as well as deliciously creative crafts, even letting the baristas have a say in creations.

However, there are still some qualms I have with the shop. Most notably, I wish the owner would focus more of his energy on doing coffee EXTREMELY well; I don't understand the eclectic assortment of random goods spews across the shop, and I doubt it turns enough of a profit to warrant the space it takes up. No one comes to perc for soap, pasta, popcorn, or lotion, so quit pouring resources into those things. I get it: Sean wants to support local businesses, and I do too! But support local businesses that are in/complimenting your industry. The daily pastries and truffles are great.
